    • Enum Constant Detail

      • turtles

        public static final TurtleKit.Option turtles
        Used to launch turtles. This option can be used from the command line or using the main method of TurtleKit. 
         SYNOPSIS
        --turtles TURTLE_CLASS_NAME[,NB][;OTHERS]

        • TURTLE_CLASS_NAME: the turtle class to launch
        • NB (integer optional): number of desired instances
         DESCRIPTION
        The optional parameters could be used to (1) launch several different types of turtles and (2) specify the number of desired instances of each type. 
         DEFAULT VALUE100000
        Default value is "null", meaning that no turtle has to be launched.

        Default values for the optional parameters are

        • NB : 1
         EXAMPLES
        • --turtles myPackage.MyTurtle
        • --turtles myPackage.MyTurtle,2000
        • --turtles myPackage.MyTurtle,30000;other.OtherTurtle,40000

      • startSimu

        public static final TurtleKit.Option startSimu
        If set to true, the simulation is started automatically. Default is Environment

      • viewers

        public static final TurtleKit.Option viewers
        Specify the viewer classes to launch. If set to null, no viewer will be launched. Several viewers could be set by separating their name with a ";"

      • fastRendering

        public static final TurtleKit.Option fastRendering
        If set to true, viewers will be launched in asynchronous display mode : faster viewing

      • cuda

        public static final TurtleKit.Option cuda
        If set to true, TurtleKit will try to use Nvidia Cuda for computing pheromones dynamics and random numbers, thus optimizing the simulation performances, especially when several pheromones are used. This requires the Cuda toolkit to be installed on the host. See https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads for more information

      • endTime

        public static final TurtleKit.Option endTime
        Specify the time at which the simulation should stop and quit
